# Variant System and Product Modeling

Variants are a critical differentiator in this platform.

## Variant system requirements

Variants must support:
- multiple option groups
- multiple option values
- clear combination logic
- variant-level SKU
- variant-level price
- variant-level compare-at price
- variant-level stock
- variant-level stock alert
- variant-level image relationship
- future variant-level custom fields

## Product modeling requirements

The platform must support:
- simple products
- variant products
- service products
- digital products
- future subscription-style products

Do not hardcode assumptions that all products are physical or simple.

## Merchant UX rule

Variant handling must be easier than competing platforms.

Merchants must be able to understand:
- what the option groups are
- what values belong to each group
- what combinations exist
- what price/stock belongs to each variant
- what image belongs to which variant

## Data integrity rule

Never allow:
- duplicate option values in the same group
- duplicate variant combinations
- ambiguous default variant behavior
- unsafe variant/image linkage
- orphaned option/variant relationships

## Day 15 and Day 16 rule

Day 15 should stabilize variant structure and merchant usability.
Day 16 should implement variant import on top of that structure.

Do not skip structural clarity and jump straight into import hacks.